main event: Two moving star-like light sources were observed over Bismarck, North Dakota, on November 26, 1968.
interesting points: The lights were seen traveling north and south,The observer initially thought they were satellites due to their speed and appearance,There were multiple witnesses from the Bismarck control tower,The sighting lasted approximately 6 minutes before the lights disappeared,No physical evidence was found after the sighting.
sighted object: two star-like light sources in the sky
witness description: Airport traffic controllers with significant experience
